  "bench_knowledge": [
    "Liquids with freeze points at or above 15\u00b0C (DMSO ~19\u00b0C, glycerol ~18\u00b0C) can solidify partially or fully in a 4\u00b0C cold room or on ice. Pipetting a partially-solidified liquid causes systematic volume errors. The physical_state guard prevents the rule from misfiring on solids whose melting point happens to be reported in freeze_point_C (e.g. NaOH pellets, PFA powder).",
    "DMSO rapidly penetrates intact skin and carries dissolved solutes transdermally, making skin contact with DMSO drug stocks a real toxicity exposure route. Polystyrene is leached by DMSO over hours-to-days; use glass or polypropylene for stock storage."
  ],
